        writing:
          "As far as coding goes, I did a little bit of work on the scroller game where I learned how to add events to an animation, which was pretty cool and I can definitely see coming in handy. I also learned a little more above navmesh areas, I was encountering a glitch where the player animation would not stop playing because it's condition that it reaches the target position was not met. This was due to the overlarge margin on the navmesh where there was an obstacle. After messing with the voxel size and humanoid radius it runs much better. I'm really glad I got this figured out. I need to focus on the inventory system, but still not sure exactly how I want it to look. Maybe I will end up waiting until I have a better idea of what the objects will be ...",
