        id: 95,
        name: "",
        url: "",
        abovewriting: "I learned how to create custom multiple color fonts in Unity. Here are the steps.",
        belowwriting:
          '(1) Create pngs in a 256x256px canvas in procreate with whatever images I want. (2) paste into Calligraphr template. (3) Download as otf. (4) Import font into Unity assets. (5) Apply settings in inspector and "create editable copy". This will create a few additional files in the project folder. (6) Find the texture2D/sprite file that looks like the picture in step 6 below. (7) Right click to reveal in finder or drag a copy somewhere. (8) Open in procreate or photoshop and apply the individual images over their respective spots. (9) Replace the original image in the project folder with this one and select it within the font asset material. (10) It can now be used in the project! Note: this only works for legacy text, but the black and white calligraphr version will work for both.',
