        abovewriting:
          "I've been struggling with this idea of capturing/getting the torso to return to the home/where its head is. I made this navmesh surface walkable area in tandem with the built in \"corners\" positioning system to get the character to animate its walk as it navigates the maze, so I thought that would be a cool effect to use here. But, I can't quite get the concept right. What happens if you play the piano successfully, vs unsuccessfully? Is there a dialogue that prompts a chase? multiple outcomes for this dialogue? Do you start to play as the torso, running away from your previous self? I liked the idea of this, but after implementing it thought it was too confusing to switch characters on the player like that, it felt forced.",
        belowwriting:
          'One thing I did create is a system of tracking "points" in the conversation with the torso, so that depending on the sum total of your responses you either get a positive or negative reaction from it which I think I could use in the future. I was able to modify my dialogue related scripts so that multiple different events can be triggered within a dialogue (before it only had the capability of one) via unity events I can assign in the inspector. That\'s been saving me a lot of time. That in tandem with using animation events in tandem with a simple unity events trigger script has been huge and widely used now for me.',
